---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'Living in New Braunfels, TX | What to Expect';
const pageDescription = 'What life in New Braunfels, TX is really like — commutes to San Antonio and Austin, weather, cost of living, culture, growth, and who this Hill Country city suits.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/new-braunfels/living-in-new-braunfels' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'New Braunfels', url: '/new-braunfels' },
    { name: 'Living in New Braunfels', url: '/new-braunfels/living-in-new-braunfels' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="nb-hero">
      <div class="nb-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="nb-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/new-braunfels/">New Braunfels</a> <span>/</span> <span>Living Here</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Living in <span style="color:#FF1616;">New Braunfels</span></h1>
        <p>What daily life actually looks like — beyond the brochure</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Daily Life -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What to <span class="accent">Expect</span></h2>
        <p class="nb-page-intro">New Braunfels is growing fast, but it still holds onto the things that made people want to live here in the first place. It's not a suburb — it's its own city with its own identity. Here's an honest look at what living here is actually like.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Culture & Lifestyle -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Culture & <span class="accent">Lifestyle</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="living__grid">
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Gruene & the River</h3>
            <p>Gruene Historic District is the cultural anchor — live music at Gruene Hall, local shops, wine tasting, and the Guadalupe River. Tubing season brings crowds in summer, but locals learn to navigate around it. The river culture is a real part of daily life here, not just a tourist attraction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Downtown & Local Scene</h3>
            <p>Downtown New Braunfels has its own personality — German bakeries, local restaurants, the Comal River, and Landa Park. First Fridays bring people out, and the farmers market is a weekend staple. It feels like a real town, not a manufactured one.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Outdoor Living</h3>
            <p>Between the rivers, Natural Bridge Caverns, Canyon Lake, and the Hill Country trails, outdoor activities are a daily option — not a weekend trip. The climate supports year-round outdoor living, though summers are hot and dry (expect 95-100+ from June through September).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__card">
            <h3>Community Events</h3>
            <p>Wurstfest in the fall, Wassailfest in December, and a steady calendar of local events keep the community connected. The German heritage is still visible in the architecture, food, and festivals — it's part of the city's character.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Practical Realities -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Practical <span class="accent">Realities</span></h2>
          <p>The things you should know before committing</p>
        </div>
        <div class="living__realities">
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Commute</h3>
            <p>San Antonio is roughly 30-40 minutes south on I-35 (outside rush hour). Austin is 45-60 minutes north. Rush hour adds time, and I-35 construction is a constant. Many residents work remotely or have flexible schedules. If you're commuting daily to downtown Austin, factor in the drive honestly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Growth & Traffic</h3>
            <p>New Braunfels is one of the fastest-growing cities in Texas. That means new retail, restaurants, and amenities are coming — but it also means construction, traffic on I-35 and FM 306, and neighborhoods that are still being built out. The city is actively investing in infrastructure, but growth is outpacing it in some areas.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Weather</h3>
            <p>Mild winters are a real draw. Spring and fall are excellent. Summers are hot — consistently in the mid-to-upper 90s from June through September. If you're coming from a cooler climate, be prepared. Air conditioning is a requirement, not a luxury.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__reality">
            <h3>Tourism Seasons</h3>
            <p>Summer brings tubing crowds to the rivers and visitors to Schlitterbahn and Gruene. Weekends from May to September can feel busy in certain areas. Locals learn the patterns and adjust. Outside of peak season, the city settles into a quieter rhythm.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Best Fit -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Who <span class="accent">Fits Here</span></h2>
          <p>New Braunfels works well for certain lifestyles — here's how different buyers tend to experience it</p>
        </div>
        <div class="living__fit-grid">
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Families</h3>
            <p>Strong school districts, safe neighborhoods, parks, rivers, and a community-oriented culture make this a top choice for families. Master-planned communities offer pools, playgrounds, and proximity to schools.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Commuters</h3>
            <p>If you work in San Antonio, the commute is manageable. Austin commuters should consider the drive carefully. The south side of the city and I-35 corridor provide the quickest highway access for daily commutes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Retirees</h3>
            <p>No state income tax, lower cost of living than major metros, healthcare access in San Antonio, and a pace of life that slows down without feeling isolated. Several communities cater specifically to 55+ buyers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="living__fit">
            <h3>Remote Workers</h3>
            <p>If you work from home, New Braunfels is hard to beat. Hill Country views, lower housing costs, strong internet infrastructure in newer communities, and proximity to two airports when you need to travel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Additional Living Info -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div style="max-width:800px;">
          <h2>Shopping, Dining, and <span class="accent">Daily Conveniences</span></h2>
          <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">New Braunfels has grown significantly in terms of retail and dining options. The I-35 corridor through the city features major retailers including HEB, HEB Plus, Target, Walmart, Home Depot, Lowe's, and Costco. For dining, you will find everything from local favorites like Krause's Cafe and the Gristmill River Restaurant to national chains and fast-casual spots. The Gruene Historic District offers a more curated selection of local restaurants, wine tasting rooms, and unique shops.</p>
          <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Healthcare access is solid and improving. Resolute Health Hospital is the primary full-service facility in New Braunfels, offering emergency services, surgical suites, and specialty care. For more specialized medical needs, the San Antonio Medical Center — one of the largest medical complexes in the country — is about 30 minutes south. New clinics and medical offices are opening regularly along the I-35 corridor to serve the growing population.</p>
          <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">One practical consideration that many newcomers appreciate is the utility setup. New Braunfels Utilities (NBU) provides electricity, water, and wastewater services for most of the city. Residents outside city limits may use GVEC Electric Cooperative or other providers. Internet service is available through Spectrum, AT&T, and GVTC Communications, with fiber options in many newer neighborhoods.</p>
          <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.8;font-size:0.95rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Overall, daily life in New Braunfels strikes a balance between small-town charm and modern convenience. The city is large enough to have everything you need, but small enough that you will run into familiar faces at the grocery store. It is a community that values its history while actively building for the future.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Living in New Braunfels</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is the cost of living in New Braunfels compared to Austin?</summary>
            <p>New Braunfels is significantly more affordable than Austin. The median home price is lower, property taxes in Comal County are below Travis County rates, and everyday expenses like groceries and utilities are comparable or slightly lower. Many remote workers and commuters choose New Braunfels specifically because they can maintain a similar quality of life at a fraction of the housing cost of Austin.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How bad is the traffic on I-35?</summary>
            <p>I-35 through New Braunfels carries heavy traffic, especially during rush hour and summer weekends. TxDOT has ongoing improvement projects to widen the highway and improve interchanges, but construction itself adds to congestion in the short term. If your daily routine avoids I-35, the traffic impact is minimal. For commuters, the south side of town provides the quickest highway access to San Antonio.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is New Braunfels safe?</summary>
            <p>New Braunfels has a lower crime rate than both San Antonio and Austin. The city is served by the New Braunfels Police Department and the Comal County Sheriff's Office. As with any growing city, crime rates vary by neighborhood, but overall the area is considered safe and family-friendly. Gated communities and master-planned neighborhoods with HOA-managed security are available for buyers who prioritize that.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Not Sure Which Area <span class="accent">Fits You</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Tell me about your lifestyle, commute, and priorities — I'll help you narrow down the neighborhoods and areas that make the most sense.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="/new-braunfels/neighborhoods/" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Neighborhoods</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Talk Through Areas That Fit</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/guadalupe-river.png" />

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to discuss which areas fit my lifestyle..." />
  <Footer />

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the cost of living in New Braunfels compared to Austin?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "New Braunfels is significantly more affordable than Austin with lower median home prices, lower property taxes in Comal County, and comparable everyday expenses."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How bad is the traffic on I-35?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "I-35 carries heavy traffic during rush hour and summer weekends. TxDOT has ongoing improvement projects. If your daily routine avoids I-35, the impact is minimal."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is New Braunfels safe?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "New Braunfels has a lower crime rate than both San Antonio and Austin. The area is considered safe and family-friendly, with gated communities available for buyers who prioritize security."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .nb-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/comal-river.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .nb-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .nb-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .nb-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .nb-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  /* Grid Cards */
  .living__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__card {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .living__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .living__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Realities */
  .living__realities {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__reality {
    border-left: 3px solid #FF1616;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background: #fafafa;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .living__reality h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .living__reality p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Fit Grid */
  .living__fit-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .living__fit {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .living__fit h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .living__fit p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .living__grid,
    .living__fit-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
